18#include "QRErrorCorrectionLevel.h"
19
20#include <cassert>
21
22namespace ZXing {
23namespace QRCode {
24
25const wchar_t* ToString(ErrorCorrectionLevel l)
26{
27 assert(l != ErrorCorrectionLevel::Invalid);
28 static const wchar_t* const LEVEL_STR[] = { L"L", L"M", L"Q", L"H", nullptr };
29 return LEVEL_STR[static_cast<int>(l)];
30}
31
32ErrorCorrectionLevel ECLevelFromString(const char* str)
33{
34 switch (str[0])
35 {
36 case 'L': return ErrorCorrectionLevel::Low;
37 case 'M': return ErrorCorrectionLevel::Medium;
38 case 'Q': return ErrorCorrectionLevel::Quality;
39 case 'H': return ErrorCorrectionLevel::High;
40 default: return ErrorCorrectionLevel::Invalid;
41 }
42}
43
44ErrorCorrectionLevel ECLevelFromBits(int bits)
45{
46 static const ErrorCorrectionLevel LEVEL_FOR_BITS[] = { ErrorCorrectionLevel::Medium, ErrorCorrectionLevel::Low, ErrorCorrectionLevel::High, ErrorCorrectionLevel::Quality };
47 return LEVEL_FOR_BITS[bits & 0x3];
48}
49
50int BitsFromECLevel(ErrorCorrectionLevel l)
51{
52 assert(l != ErrorCorrectionLevel::Invalid);
53 static const int BITS[] = { 1, 0, 3, 2, -1 };
54 return BITS[(int)l];
55}
56
57} // QRCode
58} // ZXing
